<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,541,1433]" pageId="5" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1372,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="137">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[339,610,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sopubiae">
<emphasis box="[339,610,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="137">Afrosmicronyx sopubiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from the other species of the genus by its thick rostrum and its two distinct whitish spots near the middle of each elytron.
</paragraph>
